Inspections of your records and inventory can be preformed during the
&quot;normal business hours&quot; that you state when you apply for/renew your
FFL.  With a Type 03 (Collector of Curio and Relics) you usually don't
have business hours, so the BATF has to make an appointment with you.
The same *may* be true of a Type 01 (Dealer in Firearms other than
Destructive Devices) when you applied as a gunsmith and listed your
hours &quot;by appointment&quot; on the application.

Of course you may also get an &quot;inspection&quot; at any time during a bona
fide criminal investigation.

Bottom line, if you have a problem with a friendly visit from the
feds, you probably shouldn't be (or aren't) legally dealing in
firearms in the first place.  ;-)
