With all due respect, &quot;Class III&quot; refers to the SOT &quot;dealer in NFA
weapons&quot; class, but has nothing to do with an *individual* owning one.
The proper term you should be using is Title 2, which defines NFA
weapons under the GCA.

SOT Class 1 - importer of NFA firearms
SOT Class 2 - manufacturer of NFA firearms
SOT Class 3 - dealer in NFA firearms

Class 1 and 2 may also deal in NFA firearms.

But none of the three are necessary for an individual to *own* a full
auto.
